The paper deals with the study of control in elections, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of computational social choice (cs.SI). The paper also introduces new partition models, which involve the partitioning of sets, and this is a topic that is closely related to the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) as it studies how different actors can manipulate the outcome of an election. Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of analyzing these new partition models, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.SI, in that order.
